The students are getting familiar with presenting scientific text according to the rules of Estonian grammar. With the help of his/her supervisor, the student complies the literature summary of his/her research work, and presents it at the seminar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give the students experience in compilation of a literature summary necessary for the completion of the research work. The development of the oral and written communicative skills of students in Estonian will be pursued.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the student is expected to: 1.	Be able to compile a grammatically correct written text for the chosen field of research;  2.	Be able to compile an exhaustive referative summary of literature considering a certain scientific problem; 3.	Within the defined limits, be able to present in Estonian a summary of a certain scientific problem.
